Chess GUI

Files:
- chess_gui.py

Run:
- python chess_gui.py

What it does:
- Displays a clickable chess board
- Lets you move pieces manually
- Imports and exports FEN
- Sends the current FEN to your C++ executable via stdin

Expected input for your C++ code:
position fen <current_fen>

Example C++ main:
- read a line from stdin
- parse the FEN
- print a reply such as:
  bestmove e2e4

Notes:
- This GUI does not validate legal chess moves yet
- It is designed as a clean front-end that can pass piece positions into your C++ code